{
  "text": "JDGs refer to the gene subset whose joint discriminatory power is maximum among all the subsets of the same size selected from a gene pool (e.g., IDGs). The key is the consideration of the correlation (or dependence) between genes and their joint discriminatory power. We use multidimensional wFC as the measure of the class separability in JDG selection. The wFC of JDG can be defined by [CITATION_1] ",
